HEADWORD: Monothelite
<hw>Mo*noth"e*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/;
<grk>mo`nos</grk> alone, only + <?/, <?/, to will, be willing: cf. F.
<ets>monoth⟦eacute⟧lite</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One
of an ancient sect who held that Christ had but one will as he had but
one nature. Cf. <er>Monophysite</er>.</def>
<rj><au>Gibbon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
